Important Note: Used predicted colabfold structure because protein is from a virus. We are looking for the HIV Env protein, (group M subtype/clade A). The BG520 Env protein has not been studied as much as BF520, so a BF520 structure is the best option. However, the alphafold database and the pdb have no suitable structures. The PDB 6B0N is the closest, but it is too short, and has gaps and swaps relative to the DMS and alignment.

Hugh K Haddox, Adam S Dingens, Sarah K Hilton, Julie Overbaugh, Jesse D Bloom (2018) Mapping mutational effects along the evolutionary landscape of HIV envelope eLife 7:e34420 https://doi.org/10.7554/eLife.34420
BF520 is an HIV strain, and the structure of BF520's env protein has not been studied, whereas the structure of BG505's env protein has been. However, the structure of  "BG505 and BF520 env are identical at 721 of the 836 pairwise-alignable protein sites", so it may be reasonable to use BG505 structure.
